@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #EBF4FB
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #2E86AB
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #2E86AB
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E8F8F5
skinparam NoteBorderColor #1ABC9C
skinparam SequenceDividerBackgroundColor #D5E8D4
skinparam SequenceDividerBorderColor #82B366

title **Phase 2 · Séquence — Feature Engineering & Preprocessing sklearn**

actor "Dev" as DEV

box "Python Process" #EBF4FB
  participant "phase2_feature\n_engineering" as P2
  participant "Feature\nConfigurator" as FC
end box

box "Filesystem" #F0FFF4
  participant "data/interim\n(CSV)" as FI
  participant "data/processed\n(CSV)" as FP
  participant "models/\npreprocessor/" as FM
end box

box "Services" #FFF8E8
  participant "PostgreSQL\n:5432" as PG
end box

== STEP 1 · Chargement Données ==
DEV -> P2 : python -m phase2_feature_engineering\n--source db

P2  -> PG : SELECT * FROM v_features_engineering\nWHERE sk_id_curr IN (SELECT...LIMIT N)
PG --> P2 : df_train (~307k × 300+ cols)
P2  -> PG : SELECT * FROM v_features_engineering\nWHERE split='test'
PG --> P2 : df_test (~48k × 300+ cols)
note right of PG : Fallback : read_csv(data/interim/)\nsi --source csv

== STEP 1.5 · Sync Types Catégoriels ==
P2  -> P2 : cat_cols = REGISTRY.CATEGORICAL\ndf.astype(str).replace("None"→NaN)
note right of P2 : Anti-bug PostgreSQL\n"None" str → NaN propre

== STEP 2 · Validation REGISTRY ==
P2  -> FC  : FeatureConfigurator(registry=REGISTRY)
P2  -> P2  : REGISTRY.validate_dataframe(columns)\n→ unknown_in_df, missing_from_df

== STEP 3 · Fit sur Train (anti-leakage) ==
P2  -> FC  : config.fit(df_train)
note over FC
  Calcule et mémorise UNIQUEMENT sur train :
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  médianes → imputation NaN
  μ / σ    → StandardScaler
  IQR      → RobustScaler
  catégories → OneHotEncoder mapping
  ─────────────────────────────────────────
  ⚠️ JAMAIS appelé sur df_test
end note
FC --> P2  : config fitté (paramètres appris)

== STEP 4 · Target Encoding (optionnel) ==
P2  -> FC  : fit_target_encoding(\n  df_train, smoothing=1.0\n)
note right of FC : Colonnes haute cardinalité\nRégularisation bayésienne

== STEP 5+6 · Transform Train & Test ==
P2  -> FC  : config.transform(df_train)
FC --> P2  : X_train (sklearn-ready)
P2  -> FC  : config.get_target(df_train)
FC --> P2  : y_train (Series 0/1)
P2  -> FC  : config.transform(df_test)
FC --> P2  : X_test (mêmes colonnes)
note right of FC : Même fit appliqué sur test\n→ zéro data leakage ✅

== STEP 7 · Alignement Colonnes OHE ==
P2  -> P2  : cols_manquantes = train_cols - test_cols\n→ ajout à 0.0 dans X_test
P2  -> P2  : cols_en_trop = test_cols - train_cols\n→ drop de X_test
P2  -> P2  : X_test = X_test[X_train.columns]
note right of P2 : OHE peut créer ~50 colonnes\nabsentes du test → alignement obligatoire

== STEP 8 · Contrôles Qualité ==
P2  -> P2  : NaN résiduels ?\nVariance nulle ?\nInf values ?\nTarget distribution ?

== STEP 9 · Sauvegarde Artefacts ==
P2  -> FM  : config.save_artifacts("models/preprocessor")\n→ **preprocessor.pkl** (joblib)
note right of FM : Contient médianes + scalers\nfittés → reproductible Phase 3/4/5

== STEP 10 · Export Datasets Finaux ==
P2  -> FP  : X_train.to_csv("X_train.csv")
P2  -> FP  : X_test.to_csv("X_test.csv")
P2  -> FP  : y_train.to_csv("y_train.csv")
P2  -> FP  : df_test[sk_id_curr].to_csv("test_ids.csv")

== Résumé Artefacts ==
note over FP
  **data/processed/**
  X_train.csv  (~307k × 300 features)
  X_test.csv   (~48k  × 300 features)
  y_train.csv  (~307k valeurs 0/1)
  test_ids.csv (sk_id_curr Kaggle)
end note

note over FM
  **models/preprocessor/**
  preprocessor.pkl
  (scalers + encoders fittés)
end note

DEV <-- P2 : resultats {\n  nb_features: ~300\n  X_train.shape, X_test.shape\n  t_total\n}

note over DEV
  ⮕  Suite :
  python -m src.pipelines.phase3_model_training_mlflow
end note

@enduml
